In , which was the first game in the Wario series for the Nintendo DS, Wario is walking down the street after having stolen a Game Boy Advance and Game Boy Advance SP, but trips and drops them into a sewer hole.
Wario is one of the original six playable characters and has been a playable character in every Mario Party game, with the exception of Mario Party Advance, where only Mario, Luigi, Princess Peach, and Yoshi are playable.
Wario appears as a playable character in Super Mario 64 DS for the Nintendo DS, but he must be unlocked using Luigi.
